        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 2 at 5:08AM EST by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>WEATHER...

* Areas of dense freezing fog will impact the area through the
morning commute. Temperatures ranging between 14 and 19 degrees
will allow moisture to freeze on some untreated roadways.

IMPACTS...

* Fog in contact with the ground may freeze on roads leading to
slippery conditions particularly on bridges, exit ramps and
overpasses.

* Dense fog will reduce visibilities to one quarter mile or less
at times. Rapid fluctuations of visibility will occur.
</description>
        <instruction>* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for variable
driving conditions by slowing down and allowing extra time.

* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</instruction>
